Sasini Ltd. (STCL) , a Kenyan tea and coffee
producer, advanced the most in two months after tea prices rose
at the latest auction of the leaf.  The stock climbed for a second day, adding 2.8 percent, the
most since Nov. 10, to close at 12.95 shillings at 3 p.m. in
Nairobi, the capital.  African tea prices mostly rose at a weekly sale in Mombasa,
 Kenya , James Finlay (Mombasa) Ltd. said in an e-mailed statement
